Clinton Urges Mideast Cease-Fire
WASHINGTON [AP ] - President Clinton urged Israelis and Palestinians to undertake an immediate cease-fire after a new outbreak of bloodshed and called on both sides to condemn all acts of violence .
``Now is the time to stop the bloodshed , to restore calm , to return to dialogue and ultimately to the peace process ,'' the president said Thursday afternoon in the White House Rose Garden .
